examples.en: The sea breeze blows furiously.
The tyre blows out / goes flat.
Blows were exchanged.
Gustily blows the wind.
The fuse blows / blows out.
A mine blows up / explodes.
A hurricane blows itself out.
It's an ill wind that blows no good.
Quick, catch my hat before it blows away!
They almost came to blows over the money.
The boxer took several blows to the head.
He landed several blows on his opponent's head.
This new information blows his theory sky-high.
He opens the door and a flurry of snow blows in.
She attacked the man, raining blows on his head and shoulders.
He always blows up his adventures to make them seem better than they were.
The flint instruments of oval shape have been mostly worked by gentle blows.
Dave Milton is a school librarian who also blows jazz tenor with the New Jazz Orchestra.
Furl the sail before it blows to tatters.
The door yielded to repeated blows with a battering ram
